data.enText: having or showing no interest in sb/sth
The government cannot afford to be indifferent to public opinion.

data.chText: 电影节的影片一如既往的良莠不齐——有优秀的、低劣的和一般的。
data.enText: The festival has the usual mixture of movies─ good, bad and indifferent .

data.chText: 他满不在乎地耸了耸肩。

ex.chText: 她的来信多数都是既没有人情味又模式化的。
ex.enText: Most of the letters from her were impersonal and formal.

ex.chText: 他的同事们都知道他是一个冷漠的人。
ex.enText: All his colleagues knew him as an impersonal man.

synonyms.bx: 指没有人情味、不友好的。

ex.chText: 他这个人一直和邻居很疏远。
ex.enText: He is a man who stays aloof from his neighbours.

ex.chText: 她外表冷漠，因此几乎没什么朋友。
ex.enText: She has few friends due to her aloof exterior.

synonyms.bx: 指主观上不愿意和别人多说话的，强调不合群，含不友好之意，通常作表语，常后接介词 from。

ex.enText: He became apathetic after his failure.

ex.chText: 她毫无兴趣，甚至连动都不想动。
ex.enText: She feels too apathetic to even move.

synonyms.bx: 指对某事物或某种状况不感兴趣、不愿努力作出改变的。

ex.enText: She is always cold to others.

ex.chText: 他的声音冷冰冰的，致使她不敢告诉他真相。
ex.enText: His voice was so cold that she didn't have the guts to tell him the truth.

ex.chText: 她在聚会上对每一个人都很冷淡。
ex.enText: She was cold towards everyone at the party.

synonyms.bx: 指没有同情心、幽默感等正常的情感且待人不友善的。

ex.chText: 总统访问日本时受到了冷遇。
ex.enText: The president received a cool welcome when he visited Japan.

synonyms.bx: 指不友好的，也可指没有兴趣或热情的。

ex.chText: 没人明白她为什么对他这么冷淡。
ex.enText: Nobody knew why she was so indifferent to him.

ex.chText: 她对这个话题完全没兴趣。
ex.enText: She was absolutely indifferent to this topic.

ex.chText: 他对周围的女孩们毫不在意。
ex.enText: He is indifferent to the girls around him.

synonyms.bx: 指对某人或某事物漠不关心、毫无兴趣的，常后接介词 to。

tr: showing no care or concern in attitude or action
example: indifferent to the sufferings of others
indifferent to her plea

tr: not mattering one way or the other
example: whether you choose to do it or not is a matter that is quite immaterial (or indifferent)
what others think is altogether indifferent to him

tr: marked by a lack of interest
example: an apathetic audience
the universe is neither hostile nor friendl

tr: neither too great nor too little
example: a couple of indifferent hills to climb
an indifferent performance
a gifted painter but an indifferent actor
her work at the office is passable
a so-so golfer
feeling only so-so
prepared a tolerable dinner
a tolerable working knowledge of French

tr: characterized by a lack of partiality
example: a properly indifferent jury
an unbiasgoted account of her family problems

tr: marked by no especial liking or dislike or preference for one thing over another
example: indifferent about which book you would give them
was indifferent to their acceptance or rejection of her invitation

tr: having only a limited ability to react chemically
example: inert matter
an indifferent chemical in a reaction

tr: fairly poor to not very good
example: has an indifferent singing voice
has indifferent qualifications for the job

value.def: If you accuse someone of being indifferent to something, you mean that they have a complete lack of interest in it.

example.ex: People have become indifferent to the suffering of others.
example.tran: 人们对别人的痛苦已经变得无动于衷。

example.ex: ...the row over the police's indifferent attitude to the killings.
example.tran: 严厉谴责警方对杀戮无动于衷的态度

value.tran: 不感兴趣的;不关心的;冷淡的

example.ex: 'Not that it matters,' said Tench indifferently.

value.def: If you describe something or someone as indifferent, you mean that their standard or quality is not very good, and often quite bad.

example.ex: She had starred in several very indifferent movies...
example.tran: 她主演过几部表现非常一般的电影。

example.ex: Much of the food we eat is of very poor or indifferent quality.
example.tran: 我们吃的许多食物质量要么很差,要么很一般。

value.tran: (水平或质量)一般的,平庸的，差的

example.ex: ...an eight-year-old girl who reads tolerably and writes indifferently.
example.tran: 阅读尚可、写作很一般的 8 岁女孩
